11.3 Which Image to Retag at Main Merge — HEAD^2
When release/* → main (or hotfix/* → main) merges, the pipeline running on main is a push/merge pipeline, so CI_MERGE_REQUEST_SOURCE_BRANCH_SHA is empty (it exists only in MR pipelines). The durable way to identify the tested image is the second parent of the merge commit:
# Runs on the main push/merge pipeline after release/* or hotfix/* merged.
# Requires MERGE-COMMIT method (--no-ff): main's new commit has two parents.
#   HEAD    = merge commit on main
#   HEAD^1  = previous main tip
#   HEAD^2  = source branch tip  ← the tested release/hotfix image

SRC_SHA=$(git rev-parse --short HEAD^2)
Why HEAD^2 and not git rev-parse origin/release/...: if the release branch is auto-deleted on merge, origin/release/... no longer exists when the main pipeline runs. HEAD^2 reads the merge commit itself, which permanently records the source tip — it works whether or not the branch was deleted.
11.4 Mandatory Merge Method
release/* → main and hotfix/* → main MUST use merge-commit method (--no-ff). Fast-forward and squash produce a single-parent commit with no HEAD^2, breaking the retag lookup. Configure in GitLab: Settings → Merge requests → Merge method → Merge commit. This also gives cleaner audit history (the merge commit explicitly links main to the exact tested tip).
11.5 Retag Job — With Anti-Rebuild Guard
# ── Main-merge retag job (release/* → main) ──────────────────────────────
SRC_SHA=$(git rev-parse --short HEAD^2)                    # tested release tip
SRC_BRANCH=<release-branch-name>                           # from merge metadata
SRC_IMAGE="artifactory.jfrog.sbi/itepaypg-sbiepay2-docker-local/app/backend/${SERVICE}:${SRC_BRANCH}-${SRC_SHA}"

# GUARD: the tested image MUST already exist. If not, do NOT build — fail loudly.
if ! jfrog rt search "${SRC_IMAGE#*/}" | grep -q .; then
  echo "ERROR: tested image ${SRC_IMAGE} not found. Retag must not rebuild. Aborting."
  exit 1
fi

# Compute SemVer (type from branch name, highest prod tag, race-safe retry) — see §10
NEW_SEMVER=$(compute_semver)          # e.g. 1.3.0

# Retag the SAME digest — no rebuild
docker pull  "$SRC_IMAGE"
docker tag   "$SRC_IMAGE"  "...:${NEW_SEMVER}"
docker push  "...:${NEW_SEMVER}"
The guard enforces "retag only, never build at main merge." If the tested image is missing, the job fails rather than silently rebuilding (which would break "tested = deployed").
